snippet.textDisplay:
The first time I knew Cirque du soleil was in 2012, when I watched ZAIA in Venetian, Macau. I instantly become a fans! It was a great experience of watching, what an incredible show! Everything is in detail, the story, the acrobats, costumes, make up, the light, music, etc... perfect!
Then I watched KOOZA in 2017 at MBS, Singapore. It was a cool show too, 8/10 but not as great as ZAIA 10/10. It makes me wonder why do ZAIA had been stopped??? I wish it's coming back because I love it so much, and I wish I would watch it later.. maybe in 2021, maybe somewhere in Asia.
Love from Indonesia ❤
snippet.textOriginal:

Thank you for bringing us your incredible performances! You are a Canadian legend, an institution! & to each performer they are amazing & a part of something outstandingly special! I get to as many shows I can make when you pass through & while I've been on the road.
Now my question is, why is the quality of this upload so far behind that of your previous weeks' upload?
Have you degraded your sound quality to mono for a reason? Is there a reason it is limited to 360p on my tv? I had no problems with last week's upload, March 27th's, playing in stereo & 720p
This is how you're restricting the channel on different devices. Shame. I can't watch it as it detracts too much from the spectacle.
